!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

mouse /maʊs/

(mice) 

1. N-COUNT A mouse is a small, furry animal with a long tail. 鼠 

例： ...a mouse running in a wheel in its cage. …笼子里一只踩着转轮跑的老鼠。 

2. N-COUNT A mouse is a device that is connected to a computer. By moving it over a flat surface and pressing its buttons, you can move the cursor around the screen and do things without using the keyboard. 鼠标 

例： Her message had been written; all she had to do was click the mouse. 她的信息已经写好；她要做的只是点击鼠标。

</div>

